  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dba\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dda\u0db1\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Two more grain ships leave Ukraine",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Turkey's Defense Ministry says two more ships carrying grain have left Ukraine's Chornomorsk port.",
        "The total number of vessels to leave Ukraine's Black Sea ports under a UN grain export deal will rise to 27.",
        "The ships Zumrut Ana and MV Ocean S, which were cleared to depart on August 20, were carrying 6,300 tonnes of sunflower oil and 25,000 tonnes of wheat respectively, the Joint Coordination Center set up to ensure their safe passage said in a statement.",
        "Ukraine's Seaport Authority said on Saturday that three Ukrainian ports had started loading food for seven ships. It will transport 66,500 tons of wheat, corn and sunflower oil.",
        "Ukraine's grain exports have fallen since the start of the war as its Black Sea ports closed a vital shipping route. This led to rising global food prices and fears of shortages in Africa and the Middle East.",
        "At the end of July, however, the UN and Turkey opened three Black Sea ports under an agreement brokered by Moscow and Kiev for Black Sea grain transport.",
        "Ukraine's infrastructure minister, Oleksandr Kubrakov, said on Friday that 10 more cargo ships were preparing to load and ship grain at Ukrainian Black Sea ports.",
        "He said that 25 ships have already been dispatched from the three Ukrainian ports, carrying 630,000 tons of agricultural products."
      ],
